# Phase 3: Code Quality & Internationalization вАФ `v1.5.0` (Deep Dive)

> **Reviewer Role**: Senior WordPress + WooCommerce developer and Google Maps development expert (10+ years)

---

## Why Phase 3 Matters

Phases 1 and 2 fixed critical security and architecture issues. The plugin is now **functionally correct** and **WooCommerce-compliant**. But it's not **distributable**. Phase 3 transforms it from "works on my site" code into code that meets WordPress.org plugin repository standards and is maintainable long-term.

The four issues this phase addresses are all **code quality and standards** concerns:

| Issue | Impact |
|---|---|
| 520+ lines of inline JS via PHP Heredoc | No browser caching, no source maps, no minification, debugging nightmare |
| 10+ `window.*` global variables | Collision risk with other plugins, namespace pollution |
| 0% translation coverage | Plugin is English-only, unusable in non-English WooCommerce stores |
| Hardcoded `вВє` currency symbol | Breaks in any store not using Indian Rupees |

None of these are bugs вАФ the plugin works. But every one of them would be a **rejection reason** on WordPress.org, and every one makes the codebase harder to maintain, debug, and extend.

---

## 3.1 JavaScript Externalization

### The Problem

All 520+ lines of Google Maps logic live inside a PHP Heredoc string in `class-alw-frontend.php:146вАУ668`:

```php
private function get_map_js_template() {
    return <<<'JS'
(function(){
  const API_KEY = __API_KEY__;
  const STORE_LAT = __STORE_LAT__;
  // ... 520+ lines of JS ...
})();
JS;
}
```

Config values are injected via string replacement:

```php
$script = str_replace(
    array('__API_KEY__', '__STORE_LAT__', '__STORE_LNG__', ...),
    array($api_key_js, $store_lat_js, $store_lng_js, ...),
    $js_template
);
wp_add_inline_script( 'jquery', $script );
```

Additionally, there's a second inline script block вАФ the checkout blocking logic вАФ injected via `output_blocking_script()` (lines 50вАУ143) using a raw `<script>` tag in `wp_footer`.

### Why This Is a Problem

| Concern | Explanation |
|---|---|
| **No browser caching** | Inline scripts are embedded in the HTML response. They're re-downloaded and re-parsed on every single page load. An external `.js` file would be cached by the browser and served from disk on subsequent visits. |
| **No CDN support** | Inline scripts can't be served from a CDN. External files can. |
| **No source maps** | When an error occurs in 520 lines of inline JS, the browser console shows `(index):847` вАФ useless. An external file would show `alw-checkout-map.js:312` вАФ directly debuggable. |
| **No minification** | Build tools (Terser, UglifyJS) can't touch inline PHP Heredoc strings. An external `.js` file can be minified, reducing payload by ~40%. |
| **CSP violations** | Sites with Content Security Policy headers that block `unsafe-inline` scripts will break entirely. External scripts pass CSP checks via nonces or hashes. |
| **IDE support** | PHP Heredoc strings get zero JavaScript IntelliSense, linting, or syntax highlighting in most editors. A `.js` file gets full tooling. |
| **WordPress.org rejection** | The plugin review team flags large inline script blocks. They expect `wp_enqueue_script()` + `wp_localize_script()` вАФ the standard WordPress pattern. |

### The Fix: Two External JS Files + `wp_localize_script()`

WordPress has a built-in mechanism for exactly this problem: **enqueue an external script file**, then pass PHP config values to it via `wp_localize_script()`.

#### New File: `assets/js/alw-checkout-map.js`

This file will contain the entire map logic currently in the `get_map_js_template()` Heredoc. Instead of `__API_KEY__` placeholders, it reads values from a global config object passed by PHP:

```javascript
// alw-checkout-map.js
(function($, config) {
    'use strict';

    const API_KEY     = config.api_key;
    const STORE_LAT   = parseFloat(config.store_lat);
    const STORE_LNG   = parseFloat(config.store_lng);
    const FREE_KM     = parseFloat(config.free_km);
    const MAX_KM      = parseFloat(config.max_km);
    const RATE_PER_KM = parseFloat(config.rate_per_km);
    const ROUND_METHOD = config.round_method;
    const CURRENCY    = config.currency_symbol;  // вЖР No more hardcoded вВє

    // ... rest of the map logic, unchanged ...

})(jQuery, window.alw_checkout_config || {});
```

#### New File: `assets/js/alw-checkout-blocker.js`

The blocking script from `output_blocking_script()` moves here. It has no config dependencies вАФ it's purely DOM observation logic.

```javascript
// alw-checkout-blocker.js
(function() {
    'use strict';

    const PANEL_ID = 'ds-shipping-info';
    const PLACE_BTN_SELECTOR = 'form.checkout input#place_order, ...';

    // ... blocking logic unchanged ...
})();
```

#### Modified: `class-alw-frontend.php`

The `enqueue_frontend_assets()` method changes from:

```php
// BEFORE (current вАФ 30 lines of string replacement + inline injection)
$js_template = $this->get_map_js_template();
$script = str_replace(
    array('__API_KEY__', '__STORE_LAT__', ...),
    array($api_key_js, $store_lat_js, ...),
    $js_template
);
wp_add_inline_script( 'jquery', $script );
```

To:

```php
// AFTER (standard WordPress pattern вАФ clean, cacheable, debuggable)
wp_enqueue_script(
    'alw-checkout-map',
    plugin_dir_url( dirname( __FILE__ ) ) . 'assets/js/alw-checkout-map.js',
    array( 'jquery' ),
    filemtime( plugin_dir_path( dirname( __FILE__ ) ) . 'assets/js/alw-checkout-map.js' ),
    true  // Load in footer
);

wp_localize_script( 'alw-checkout-map', 'alw_checkout_config', array(
    'api_key'         => ALW_GOOGLE_API_KEY,
    'store_lat'       => ALW_STORE_LAT,
    'store_lng'       => ALW_STORE_LNG,
    'free_km'         => ALW_FREE_KM,
    'max_km'          => ALW_MAX_KM,
    'rate_per_km'     => ALW_RATE_PER_KM,
    'round_method'    => ALW_ROUND_METHOD,
    'currency_symbol' => html_entity_decode( get_woocommerce_currency_symbol() ),
    'i18n'            => array(
        'shipping_free'          => __( 'Shipping: FREE', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'shipping_label'         => __( 'Shipping', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'delivery_not_available' => sprintf(
            __( 'DELIVERY NOT AVAILABLE (beyond %s km)', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
            ALW_MAX_KM
        ),
        'enter_address'          => __( 'Enter billing address or pick location on the map to calculate shipping.', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'place_pin'              => __( 'Place the pin at exact delivery location', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'current_location'       => __( 'Current location', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'getting_location'       => __( 'Getting locationвА¶', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'geolocation_unsupported'=> __( 'Geolocation not supported.', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'location_failed'        => __( 'Could not get location.', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'location_set'           => __( 'Location set', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'use_my_location'        => __( 'Use my location for billing address', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'maps_not_ready'         => __( 'Maps not ready. Please try again.', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'cannot_compute'         => __( 'Could not compute distance. Please use the map.', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'approx_location'        => __( 'Approx location', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'selected_location'      => __( 'Selected location', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'store_label'            => __( 'Store', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'delivery_location'      => __( 'Delivery location', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
        'delivery_block_message' => __( 'Delivery not available to the selected location. Please choose a different address or contact support.', 'auto-location-woocommerce' ),
    ),
));

wp_enqueue_script(
    'alw-checkout-blocker',
    plugin_dir_url( dirname( __FILE__ ) ) . 'assets/js/alw-checkout-blocker.js',
    array(),
    filemtime( plugin_dir_path( dirname( __FILE__ ) ) . 'assets/js/alw-checkout-blocker.js' ),
    true
);
```

#### What Gets Deleted from `class-alw-frontend.php`

| Method | Lines | Action |
|---|---|---|
| `get_map_js_template()` | 146вАУ668 (522 lines) | **Delete entirely** вАФ logic moves to `alw-checkout-map.js` |
| `output_blocking_script()` | 50вАУ143 (93 lines) | **Delete entirely** вАФ logic moves to `alw-checkout-blocker.js` |

**Net effect**: `class-alw-frontend.php` shrinks from **670 lines to ~50 lines**. It becomes a thin enqueue-and-configure class вАФ exactly what it should be.

### Technical Detail: Google Maps Script Loading

The current Heredoc injects the Google Maps `<script>` tag dynamically:

```javascript
function injectMapsScript(url, id, onload, onerror) {
    var s = document.createElement('script');
    s.src = url;
    // ...
    document.head.appendChild(s);
}
```

This approach is fine and should remain in `alw-checkout-map.js`. We do **not** want to enqueue the Google Maps API via `wp_enqueue_script()` because:

1. The Maps API URL contains the store's API key вАФ it's dynamic, not a static file
2. The Maps API script requires a callback to trigger `dsInitMap()` вАФ this is handled by the existing `injectMapsScript` + polling pattern
3. Loading is conditional on the map DOM element existing

The external JS file handles its own Google Maps bootstrap вАФ this is standard practice and documented by Google.

