## 3.2 JavaScript Namespace Consolidation

### The Problem

The frontend JS creates **12 global variables** on `window`:

| # | Global Variable | Purpose | Risk |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `window._dsMapsLoaded` | Flag: Maps API loaded | вЪ†пЄП Generic `_ds` prefix |
| 2 | `window.dsMap` | Google Maps instance | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 3 | `window.dsStoreMarker` | Store marker | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 4 | `window.dsCustomerMarker` | Customer pin marker | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 5 | `window.dsGeocoder` | Geocoder instance | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 6 | `window.dsUserLocMarker` | Blue dot marker | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 7 | `window.dsUserLocCircle` | Accuracy circle | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 8 | `window.dsConnectionLine` | Dotted line | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 9 | `window.dsInitMap` | Map init callback | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 10 | `window.DS_recomputeShippingNow` | Public API: force recompute | вЪ†пЄП Generic name |
| 11 | `window.alw_checkout_config` | Config from `wp_localize_script` | вЬЕ Namespaced (new) |
| 12 | `window.ALW` | Namespace object | вЬЕ This is what we're creating |

The `ds` prefix (presumably from an older name вАФ "Distance Shipping"?) offers no collision protection. Any other plugin using `window.dsMap` or `window.dsGeocoder` would silently overwrite these.

### The Fix

Consolidate everything under `window.ALW`:

```javascript
window.ALW = window.ALW || {};

(function(ALW, $, config) {
    'use strict';

    // Private state вАФ NOT on window
    var map = null;
    var storeMarker = null;
    var customerMarker = null;
    var geocoder = null;
    var userLocMarker = null;
    var userLocCircle = null;
    var connectionLine = null;
    var mapsLoaded = false;

    // Public API вАФ accessible as ALW.recomputeShipping()
    ALW.recomputeShipping = recomputeAndShow;
    ALW.initMap = dsInitMap;
    ALW.mapsLoaded = function() { return mapsLoaded; };

    // ... rest of logic uses local variables instead of window.* ...

})(window.ALW, jQuery, window.alw_checkout_config || {});
```

**Before**: 12 global variables with generic `ds` prefix.
**After**: 1 global variable (`window.ALW`) with everything else as private local variables or properties of `ALW`.

### Impact on Other Code

The blocking script (`alw-checkout-blocker.js`) does NOT reference any `window.ds*` variables вАФ it only reads DOM elements (`#ds-shipping-info`, `#place_order`). So it requires **no changes** for namespace consolidation.

The only cross-reference is `window.dsInitMap` which is called by our own code. After renaming to `ALW.initMap`, the reference in `ensureMapInjection()` simply changes from `window.dsInitMap()` to `ALW.initMap()`.

