## 3.3 Internationalization (i18n)

### The Problem

The plugin declares `Text Domain: auto-location-woocommerce` in its header but wraps **zero** strings with translation functions. This means:

1. Translation plugins (Loco Translate, WPML, Polylang) can't discover any strings
2. The plugin is permanently English-only
3. WordPress.org would reject this вАФ translation readiness is a requirement

### What Needs Wrapping

There are two categories of user-facing strings:

#### A. PHP Strings (Backend)

These use WordPress translation functions directly:

| File | String | Function |
|---|---|---|
| `auto-location-woocommerce.php:39` | `'Auto-Location for WooCommerce requires WooCommerce...'` | `esc_html__()` |
| `auto-location-woocommerce.php:71` | `'Auto-Location Plugin Paused: Please fill in...'` | `__()` with `wp_kses()` |
| `auto-location-woocommerce.php:122` | `'We could not pinpoint your delivery location...'` | `__()` |
| `auto-location-woocommerce.php:131` | `'We do not deliver to this address...'` | `__()` with `sprintf()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:28` | `'Auto Location Settings'`, `'Auto Location'` | `__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:59вАУ66` | All field labels: `'Google Maps API Key'`, `'Store Latitude'`, etc. | `__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:73` | `'Required: Geocoding API, Maps JavaScript API...'` | `esc_html__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:76вАУ79` | Security warning text | `__()` with `wp_kses()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:117` | Rounding method labels: `'Ceil (Round Up)'`, etc. | `__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:135` | `'Save Settings'` | `__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:147` | `'Latitude must be between -90 and 90.'` | `__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:156` | `'Longitude must be between -180 and 180.'` | `__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:171` | `'Max delivery distance must be greater than 0.'` | `__()` |
| `class-alw-admin.php:175` | `'Max distance cannot be less than...'` | `__()` |
| `class-alw-checkout.php:82` | `'Delivery Map Pin: ...'` (plain text email) | `__()` |
| `class-alw-checkout.php:84вАУ85` | `'Delivery Location'`, `'Map Pin:'`, `'View exact delivery...'` | `__()` |
| `class-alw-shipping-method.php:23вАУ24` | `'Distance-Based Shipping'`, method description | `__()` |
| `class-alw-shipping-method.php:55вАУ96` | All instance form field titles and descriptions | `__()` |
| `class-alw-shipping-method.php:156вАУ159` | Shipping rate labels: `'Free вАФ ...'`, `'Distance Shipping (...)'` | `__()` with `sprintf()` |

**Total PHP strings to wrap: ~30+**

#### B. JavaScript Strings (Frontend)

JS cannot call `__()` directly. The standard WordPress solution is to pass pre-translated strings via `wp_localize_script()`. The JS code then reads them from the config object.

Current hardcoded strings in the JS Heredoc:

| Line | String | Replacement Key |
|---|---|---|
| 264 | `'DELIVERY NOT AVAILABLE (beyond ' + MAX_KM + ' km)'` | `config.i18n.delivery_not_available` |
| 267 | `'Shipping: FREE'` | `config.i18n.shipping_free` |
| 270 | `'Shipping: вВє'` | `config.i18n.shipping_label + ': ' + config.currency_symbol` |
| 275 | `'Place the pin at exact delivery location'` | `config.i18n.place_pin` |
| 367 | `'Enter billing address or use the map...'` | `config.i18n.enter_address` |
| 389 | `'Could not compute distance. Please use the map.'` | `config.i18n.cannot_compute` |
| 391 | `'Maps not ready. Please try again.'` | `config.i18n.maps_not_ready` |
| 413 | `'Approx location'` | `config.i18n.approx_location` |
| 412 | `'Selected location'` | `config.i18n.selected_location` |
| 474 | `'Store'` | `config.i18n.store_label` |
| 484 | `'Delivery location'` | `config.i18n.delivery_location` |
| 568 | `'Current location'` | `config.i18n.current_location` |
| 577 | `'Current location'` (button label) | `config.i18n.current_location` |
| 585 | `'Getting locationвА¶'` | `config.i18n.getting_location` |
| 586 | `'Geolocation not supported.'` | `config.i18n.geolocation_unsupported` |
| 594 | `'Could not get location.'` | `config.i18n.location_failed` |
| 633 | `'Use my location for billing address'` | `config.i18n.use_my_location` |
| 639 | `'Enter billing address or pick location...'` | `config.i18n.enter_address` |
| 645 | `'Geolocation not supported.'` | `config.i18n.geolocation_unsupported` |
| 647 | `'Getting locationвА¶'` | `config.i18n.getting_location` |
| 657 | `'Location set'` | `config.i18n.location_set` |
| 658 | `'Use my location for billing address'` | `config.i18n.use_my_location` |
| 662 | `'Could not get location.'` | `config.i18n.location_failed` |

Also the blocking script in `output_blocking_script()`:

| Line | String | Replacement Key |
|---|---|---|
| 64 | `'Delivery not available to the selected location...'` | Passed via `wp_localize_script` or left as fallback text |
| 136 | `'Delivery not available.'` | Same |

**Total JS strings: ~20 unique strings** (some repeated).

### How `wp_localize_script()` i18n Works

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant PHP as PHP (enqueue_frontend_assets)
    participant WP as WordPress Core
    participant Browser as Browser

    PHP->>PHP: __('Shipping: FREE', 'auto-location-woocommerce')
    Note over PHP: Returns translated string<br/>"Env√≠o: GRATIS" (Spanish)
    PHP->>WP: wp_localize_script('alw-checkout-map',<br/>'alw_checkout_config', $config)
    WP->>Browser: Injects: var alw_checkout_config = {"i18n":{"shipping_free":"Env√≠o: GRATIS",...}};
    Browser->>Browser: alw-checkout-map.js reads config.i18n.shipping_free
    Note over Browser: Shows "Env√≠o: GRATIS" in the UI
```

The translation happens in PHP (where `.po`/`.mo` files are loaded), and the already-translated string is passed to JS as data. The JS code never needs to know about locales вАФ it just reads `config.i18n.*`.

